p: Inthe United States commissioners Court before Eben Smith, United States commissioner in and for the third Judicial District of Washington Territory at Seattle, in King County.
United States of America. -vs- William Jamison Richard Daley, and William Winters.

Whereas William Jamison, Richard Daley (whose real and true name is Peter Daley) and William Winters, have been charged on oath before me, the undersigned United States commissioner in and for the 3rd Judicial District of Washington Territory at Seattle in King County, with the crime of conspiring to defraud the U.S. out of certain of its Public lands as in complaint of William F. Prosser special agent of the General Land Office of the United States, setforth, contrary to the Statutes in such cases made and provided and whereas William Jones, William H. Doyle, Peter Anderson, Fred Williams and Afred Woods, have been duly subpoenaed as witnesses in the matter of said charge
-2nd-
on behalf of the U.S. and whereas to the matter upon examination had this day before me, said named witnesses then and there being present, not having offered sufficient bail as required by me, the said commissioner in the sum of Five hundred each for their and each of their appearance at the next regular term of the District Court of the Third Judicial District of Washington Territory holding terms at Seattle and for the counties of King and Kitsap to begun and holden on the first monday of April next, then and there to testify as witnesses for and on behalf of the U.S. in the matter of the charge aforesaid: were by me then
